x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Amid all the covera=
ge and commentary, one angle currently receiving less attention than it mig=
ht=E2=80=94and that history will surely note <i>and </i>long remember=E2=80=
=94is how Biden=E2=80=99s decision offered an implicit reaffirmation of one=
 the oldest, most reliable, indeed arguably inviolate rules in Democratic p=
olitics: Never bet against <b>Nancy Pelosi</b>.<br/><br/>To say that Speake=
r Emerita Pelosi personally drove Biden out of the race overstates what too=
k place in the past three weeks=E2=80=94but not by much. Based on my report=
ing, a more precise and accurate formulation is this: If not for Pelosi, Bi=
den wouldn=E2=80=99t have been driven from the race today, and might have b=
een able to run out the clock (as was his and his team=E2=80=99s strategy) =
until his renomination was formalized at the Democratic convention in Chica=
go in mid-August.<br/><br/>It was Pelosi who
spearheaded the effort first to persuade and then to pressure Biden to step=
 aside. Though she had indispensable allies in marshaling this effort=E2=80=
=94including, crucially, <b>Chuck</b> <b>Schumer</b>, <b>Hakeem</b> <b>Jeff=
ries</b>, and <b>Barack</b> <b>Obama</b>=E2=80=94Pelosi=E2=80=99s role was =
singular in its execution and effect. Starting with her seminal doubt-casti=
ng <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2U=
ktxclJLZ0dRMkIwcEtZSXhkWVFrWnpYdVhlWT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubXNuYmMu=
Y29tL21vcm5pbmctam9lL3dhdGNoL25hbmN5LXBlbG9zaS1pdC1zLXVwLXRvLWJpZGVuLXRvLWR=
