lass in power politics as sophisticated as any I have seen in 35 years of c=
overing this stuff. She carefully and sure-handedly balanced an extraordina=
ry number of
psychic variables, emotional equities, and personal histories and agendas, =
all the while methodically and relentlessly (some would say ruthlessly) tur=
ning the screws on Biden=E2=80=94making it abundantly clear that the campai=
gn to push him off the ticket wasn=E2=80=99t going to abate and, in fact, w=
as destined to become more public, direct, and voluble (and thus more embar=
rassing to him). Indeed, more than one Democratic congressperson told me th=
at Pelosi, Schumer, Jeffries, and others were prepared, if need be, to go o=
n camera this week and call on Biden to drop out because he no longer had t=
he support of his party.<br/><br/>Biden was <u><a href=3D"https://email.puc=
